ANALYSIS.

Antipho, an elderly, well—to-do citizen of Athens, wishes his two daughters, Philumena and Pamphila, to give up their re- spective husbands, Epignomus and Pamphilippus‚ who having become impoverished have left Athens to seek their fortunes and have not been heard of for more than two years, so that they may marry wealthy men.
